<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1254,1961]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,1722,1746]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is given in homage to Dr. Ranyse Querino of the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Empresa Brasileira de Pesquisa Agropecuária</emphasis>
- EMBRAPA, collector of the specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1254,1961]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,324,1793,1818]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Variations.</emphasis>
In some 
<typeStatus box="[432,539,1794,1818]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">paratypes</typeStatus>
the pedicel has a brown spot on the dorsum, mid and hind tibiae, with the anterior and posterior surfaces yellow and an incomplete dark brown preapical ring. The surstylus is also shorter than in the 
<typeStatus box="[192,294,1865,1889]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1254,1961]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1902,1926]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[677,883,1903,1926]" class="Insecta" family="Periscelididae" genus="Neoscutops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[677,883,1903,1926]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Neoscutops minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[892,983,1902,1926]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[892,975,1902,1926]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
but can be distinguished by the yellow clypeus, larger size and characters of the male and female terminalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
